.TH DEL 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
del \- delete files or directories
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B del
.RI [ \-r ]
.IR file ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B del
removes each
.IR file .
With
.BR \-r ,
directories are removed recursively.
Without
.BR \-r ,
attempting to delete a directory is an error.
.PP
The entries
.B .
and
.B ..
are always skipped when traversing directories.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-r
Recursively delete directories and their contents.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All targets removed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments or missing target name.
.TP
.B 2
Cannot open or read directory.
.TP
.B 3
.BR remove (3)
failed for a file or directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Delete a single file:
.EX
del old.log
.EE
.TP
Recursively delete a directory:
.EX
del -r tmp/
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rm (1),
.BR mkd (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
